fg_segments: Copyright and privacy The National Library welcomes visitors from New Zealand and around the world to use its websites.
Feel free to access and link to pages and collection items here as you please.
Content Some content on this site was produced by third parties.
The Library provides a platform for this content, but does not own or necessarily endorse it.
We link to the websites of other agencies and organisations.
The Library is not responsible for the content of those sites – they are.
However, we will try to make sure our links are always going to the right place.
The Library accepts no liability or responsibility for the manner in which the information on this website is interpreted or used, or the results of such use.

Copyright Aside from collection items and third-party content, which have their own various levels of copyright and usage restrictions, copyright on all content available on this site is owned by the Crown.
Images with Crown copyright and labelled all rights reserved should not be reproduced without receiving permission from the Library.
All other Crown copyright material on this site is licensed for re-use under the Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 New Zealand licence.
Please note that this licence does not apply to any logos, emblems and trade marks on the website or to the website's design elements.
You may reproduce this Crown copyright material free of charge without further permission, as long as you:
reproduce it accurately do not use it in a derogatory or misleading way, and acknowledge the source and copyright status.
The copyright on content created by third parties is owned by them.
Before you use content created by third parties, including photographs, collection items, comments, and material from the National Union Catalogue, you need to:
check its copyright status obtain permission from the rights holder determine and meet any other requirements.
These terms do not apply to material covered by the Flags, Emblems, and Names Protection Act 1981. More information about reusing collection objects from this site.
Privacy When you use certain functions of this site we will ask for your personal information.
We will safeguard your personal information (information that identifies you as a natural person) and respect your rights under the Privacy Act 1993.
If you send us personal information (for example, your email address when asking a research question), we will only use this personal information for the purpose for which it was provided.
We will keep any personal information you provide to us secure and will not disclose it to any other parties without your prior consent.
Contact us if you have any questions or concerns personal information we hold.
As well as this, we gather statistical information on visitation to help us improve this site and our services.
This information is aggregated and non-personally identifying. It includes:

your IP address the search terms you used the pages you accessed on our site and the links you clicked on the date and time you visited the site the referring site (if any) through which you clicked through to this site your operating system (such as Windows 10, Mac OS) the type of web browser you use (such as Mozilla Firefox, Chrome, or Edge), and other incidental matters such as screen resolution, the release of your installed Flash version and the language setting of your browser.
If you would like any further information on privacy or the information that we collect, email digital-services@dia.govt.nz.
Cookies This site generates session cookies for the purpose of monitoring site usage so we can understand how to improve the service.
Cookies are also used to temporarily save your favourites.
The cookies do not collect personal information. You can disable them or clear them out of the web browser you are using to view this site without affecting your ability to use the site.
Copyright On this site you will find content with different copyright restrictions.
Some, like this page, is under Crown copyright, and can be reused as long as it isn't altered or used inappropriately, and is properly referenced.
Collection items, on the other hand, can be under current copyright or no copyright at all.
Before using this third-party content, you should check its status and obtain permission from the rights holder if applicable.
Privacy We take your privacy and your rights under the Privacy Act 1993 seriously.
Any personal information gathered as you use our site and services will only be used for those purposes, and will never be disclosed without permission or sold.
We gather statistical information to improve our site. This is all aggregated and is does not personally identify you.
It includes search terms used, number of pages visited, what browser you use, and similar data.
